'Au revoir, Paris; Hello Hollywood': Highlights from Sunday's Olympic closing ceremony

The curtain has closed on the Paris Games where Team USA completed an unforgettable journey with a total of 126 medals, including forty gold

Olympics 101: What to know with the Paris Summer Games

The 2024 Summer Games lived up to the hype. Here are key facts about athletes, events, and festivities in Paris.

What's in the medal winners box at the 2024 Olympics?

Medals were the top goal at the 2024 Olympics, but what else came in the winners box? Check out the full breakdown for winners at the Paris Games now.

Why did Paris host the 2024 Olympics? French facts to know

Paris, France hosted the Summer Games for the third time in 2024. Check out fun facts about French Olympic history now.

How old do you have to be to compete in the Olympics?

At the 2024 Summer Games, Quincy Wilson became the youngest American male track athlete in Olympic competition, at 16 years old.

When are the Olympics over? Closing ceremony date, time, more

The Paris Olympics opening ceremony set a high bar for spectacle. What will the closing ceremony bring? Fans will have to tune in to find out.

When did summer events become Olympic sports?

Popular sports like soccer and golf weren't always in the Olympics. Check out when summer sports became a part of the Olympic Games.

Summer Olympics results: U.S. gold medals by event

The U.S. has won more gold medals at the Summer Olympics than any other country. Check out 2024 gold medals by event and the all-time medal count.

Olympics Dictionary: Breaking to Dream Team, golf to rings

It's time for the 2024 Olympics! Get psyched for this summer's festivities by reflecting on top terms related to the history of the Games.

Aug. 11 Olympics schedule: Basketball, closing ceremony

On August 11th, Olympic fans can catch finals in basketball and volleyball, in addition to the closing ceremony. Check out the Paris schedule now.

USA wins men's hoops gold medal game against France and more in Paris on Saturday

Saturday at the 2024 Paris Games was headlined by Team USA's gold medal in men's basketball against France, along with the men's and women's 4x400-meter relay finals.

Aug. 10 Olympics schedule: Breaking, basketball, soccer

On August 10th, Olympic fans can catch finals in breaking, basketball, and soccer, among other exciting events. Check out the Paris schedule now.

Sha'Carri Richardson leads relay team to gold, U.S. women's hoops to play France in final and more from Friday in Paris

The U.S. women's 4x100m relay team won gold, while the men's relay team was disqualified for passing the baton outside the "takeover zone."

The complete day-by-day guide to Team GB at Paris 2024

Everything you need to know about Team GB's medal chances for the remainder of the Games.

Aug. 9 Olympics schedule: Breaking, golf, basketball

On August 9th, Olympic fans can catch breaking, golf, and women's basketball, among other exciting events. Check out the Paris schedule now.

Team USA storms back for win against Serbia and more from Paris

LeBron James, Sydney McLaughlin-Levrone and Noah Lyles are among the most recognizable names who will compete Thursday at the 2024 Paris Games.

Aug. 8 Olympics schedule: Track and field, basketball, golf

On August 8th, Olympic fans can catch track and field, golf, and basketball, among other exciting events. Check out the Paris schedule now.

Team USA women's basketball keeps 59-game streak and more from Wednesday in Paris

Several American athletes competed on their sport's biggest global stage on Wednesday at the 2024 Paris Games.

Aug. 7 Olympics schedule: Golf, volleyball, basketball

On August 7th, Olympic fans can catch golf, volleyball, and basketball among other exciting events. Check out the Paris schedule now.

Team USA men's basketball moves on to semifinal round and more from Tuesday in Paris

A handful of Americans, including Gabby Thomas, earned medals on the track, while the USWNT secured a trip to soccer's gold medal match.

Noah Lyles qualifies for 200-meter semifinal, Biles and Chiles win medals on floor and more Monday in Paris

Monday also featured a handful of knockout round matches in beach and indoor volleyball, plus the U.S. women's 3x3 basketball earned a bronze medal.

Aug. 6 Olympics schedule: Soccer, basketball, skateboarding

On August 6th, Olympic fans can catch soccer, basketball, and skateboarding, among other exciting events. Check out the Paris schedule now.

Aug. 5 Olympics schedule: Gymnastics, soccer, basketball

On August 5th, Olympic fans can catch gymnastics, soccer, and 3x3 basketball, among other exciting events. Check out the Paris schedule now.

Lyles wins 100m final, Djokovic, Scheffler strikes gold and more from Sunday at the Paris Games

Noah Lyles advanced to the 100-meter final, while a thrilling gold medal match saw Novak Djokovic add another honor to a stacked resume.

Amid barbs, Tyreek Hill challenges sprinter Noah Lyles to race

Dolphins wide receiver Tyreek Hill has taken aim at the credentials of sprinter Noah Lyles, challenging the 100-meter Olympic gold medalist to a 50-yard race on social media.

Gold medal boxer Imane Khelif hailed upon return to Algeria

With an outpouring of fans greeting her as she arrived in her hometown, Olympic gold medalist Imane Khelif extolled Algeria for backing its athletes and said she hoped to again make her country proud in the future.
